README - kbd

Last Updates April 16, 2002

--------------------------------------------------------
About:

This is a program that will map keystrokes to points in the PLC memory. Right now it is only configured for the chaser demo.

-------------------------------------------------------- 
Notes:

	- changes can be made by changing the source code.

--------------------------------------------------------
Bugs:

	- none known

--------------------------------------------------------
Todo:

	- make this versatile to load kay mappings from a file.

--------------------------------------------------------
History:

(original) Mario and Jiri - the original program was written as a quick fix for the normal KBD module that didn't work on all platforms.
April 16, 2002 (Hugh Jack) - rewritten so that it would use the process handler
